<sect2 id="sect_definingGroups" label="1">
    <title id="title_definingGroups">Defining Groups in a form</title>
    <informaltable frame="none">
        <tgroup rowsep="0" cols="2" align="left" colsep="0">
            <colspec colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec colwidth="3*"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry rowsep="1"/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Purpose</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para> A form of a <trademark>jACOB</trademark> application consists of one
                            or more groups. The groups contain the actual GUI elements. </para>
                        <para>
                            <figure id="fig_groupsInForm">
                                <title> Groups in a form</title>
                                <screenshot>
                                    <mediaobject>
                                        <imageobject>
                                            <imagedata fileref="./Screenshots/GroupsInForm.jpg" format="JPEG"/>
                                        </imageobject>
                                    </mediaobject>
                                </screenshot>
                            </figure>
                        </para>
                        <para>Each group is uniquely assigned to one <glossterm
                                linkend="tableAlias">table alias</glossterm>. In the normal case a
                            group visually goups data of the <glossterm linkend="tableAlias">table
                            alias</glossterm> tied to the group.</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Procedure</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para> Proceed the following steps to define a group in a form:</para>
                        <para>
                            <informaltable rowsep="1" colsep="1" frame="all">
                                <tgroup cols="2">
                                    <colspec align="center" colwidth="1*"/>
                                    <colspec align="left" colwidth="6*"/>
                                    <thead>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>Step</entry>
                                            <entry align="center">Procedure</entry>
                                        </row>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>1</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Select the appropriate form in the folder
                                                  <guilabel>Forms</guilabel> in the
                                                  <guilabel>Application Outline</guilabel> view.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>2</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Select the menu item
                                                  <guimenuitem>Group</guimenuitem> from the
                                                  <guibutton>DB Elements</guibutton> menu in
                                                  the form editor.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>3</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Draw a rectangle as placeholder for the group
                                                  to be defined.</para>
                                                <para>Hereafter, <trademark>jACOB</trademark>
                                                  designer will pop up a dialog asking to specify
                                                  the ancor table alias for the group.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>4</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Specify the ancor table alias and confirm your input.</para>
                                                <para>Hereupon, <trademark>jACOB</trademark>
                                                  designer will create a group in your form
                                                  labelled with the name of the ancor table. The
                                                  group automatically contains the four buttons
                                                  <guibutton>Search</guibutton>,
                                                  <guibutton>Clear</guibutton>,
                                                  <guibutton>New</guibutton> and
                                                  <guibutton>Update</guibutton>. </para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>5</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Add the desired GUI Elements to the form as
                                                  explained in the next sections.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                    </tbody>
                                </tgroup>
                            </informaltable>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Groups without default buttons</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para> You can also create groups without the four default buttons <guibutton>Search</guibutton>,
                            <guibutton>Clear</guibutton>, <guibutton>New</guibutton> and
                            <guibutton>Update</guibutton>. This will be achieved, if you just click at
                            the position you want to have the group in your form instead of drawing a
                            rectangle as a placeholder for your group.</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry/>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
</sect2>
